items.name: Kensington SafeStand iMac Keyed Locking Station
items.shortDescription: Protect your computer from theft with the Kensington SafeStand iMac Lock Station. It's good for schools, libraries and multi-user environments that need the highest level in iMac security. The Kensington computer lock delivers with this ultimate iMac security solution. It features a nearly impenetrable ClickSafe lock that has a tethered cord to keep it in place. To secure the lock, simply bolt the SafeStand directly to a desk or table and then secure it to the iMac with the ingenious Kensington SafeDome. Not only does the SafeStand complement the iMac aesthetics, it preserves all screen adjustments and swivel functions and secures corded keyboards and mice. The Kensington lock is universally compatible with both 21" and 27" iMac models that are 2010 and newer. It's sure to be a helpful gadget that will provide peace of mind in areas with high traffic use. With the Kensington SafeStand iMac Lock Station, your computer will stay safe and look just as sleek as ever.
items.longDescription: <br><b>Kensington SafeStand iMac Keyed Locking Station:</b><ul><li>Highest level of physical security for iMac</li><li>Includes nearly impenetrable ClickSafe lock head</li><li>Bolts directly to desk or table for a permanent solution</li><li>Easy to setup Kensington computer lock</li><li>Manages cables while also securing a wired keyboard and mouse</li><li>Won't interfere with screen adjustments or swivel</li><li>Sleek design complements aesthetics of the iMac</li><li>Universally compatible with both 21" and 27" iMac models, 2010 and newer</li><li>Good for schools, libraries, and multi-user environments that need high security</li></ul>

items.name: Sabrent Mini DisplayPort (Thunderbolt) to HDMI Adapter [4K Support Gold Plated] (DA-MDHA)
items.longDescription: The Sabrent Mini DisplayPort to HDMI Adapter allows you to connect your TV, computer, tablet, monitor, and other HDMI A devices to a Mini DisplayPort compatible device.  <br>  <br>  <b>Compatibility (Incomplete List)</b>  <br> - Apple MacBook, MacBook Pro, MacBook Air, iMac, Mac mini, Mac Pro  <br> - Microsoft Surface Book/Pro/Pro 2/Pro 3/Pro 4 with Windows 8 Pro or Windows 10 (NOT Surface/Surface 2 with Windows RT)  <br> - Lenovo ThinkPad X1 Carbon, X230/240s, L430/440, L530/540, T430/440, T440s, T440p, T530/540p, W530/540, Helix  <br> - Dell XPS 13/14/15/17, Latitude E7240/E7440, Precision M3800  <br> - Alienware 14/17/18  <br> - Acer Aspire R7-571/R7-571G/R7-572/R7-572G/S7-392/V5-122P/V5-552G/V5-552P/V5-552PG/V5-572P/V7-481P/V7-482PG/V7-581/V7-582P  <br> - Google Chromebook Pixel  <br> - Supports video modes up to 4K and up to 8-channel LPCM/HBR audio. Maximum available resolution is determined by your computer and display. Adapter will not allow resolutions above what your PC or HDMI display are capable of.  <br> - Supports HDCP/DPCP content protection. Note that all other devices in the playback chain must be HDCP compliant for playback of protected content such as Blu-ray.  <br>  <br>  <b><br>Note:<br></b> 1. Mini DisplayPort is NOT compatible with Macs (before 2008) that have Mini-DVI. Please check your port before purchase.  <br> 2. Macs made before 2010 are NOT able to output audio over Mini DisplayPort. More info and then check the Model Identifier field in Hardware Overview.  <br> 3. Please be aware that with an OS X Mavericks update (10.9 and later) Apple disabled 4K output on the vast majority of prevous Mac models. For a list of 4K-compatible Mac systems, please reference: https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT202856  <br> 4. This cable can only pass signal from DisplayPort to HDMI port. It is not a bi-directional cable.  <br> 5. Audio will not be passed through the adapter to the HDMI display on Macs. Samsung U28D590D not compatible with Mac systems.
